      {
        "type": "infoPanel",
        "attrs": {
          "body": "Pinch of mixed herbs.",
          "tone": "info",
          "title": "Also"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Cut the waxy potatoes into bite-sized pieces",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Add the waxy potatoes to a baking tray with a generous drizzle of olive oil, garlic, mixed herbs and a pinch of salt and pepper",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 25-30 min or until golden and crisp",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Once the potatoes have had 20 min in the oven, pat the sea bass dry and season the skin generously with salt",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Heat a large, wide-based pan with a matching lid (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat. Add a drizzle of vegetable oil."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Once hot, add the sea bass, skin-side down and cook for 3-4 min, then flip and cook for 1 min further. Tip: try not to move the sea bass around the pan, as this will prevent it from crisping up",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Add a large knob of butter with the green beans, a pinch of salt, a pinch of minced garlic and a small splash of water",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "intro": "A few of the more common issues, and what tends to fix them.",
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Salt a pinch at a time, tasting. A squeeze of lemon or splash of vinegar at the end lifts most savoury dishes.",
              "cause": "Underseasoned or no acid.",
              "symptom": "The dish tastes flat"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Pull off the heat a minute or two before you think it's done. Plate straight away, or transfer to a warmed serving dish.",
              "cause": "Carryover cooking, food keeps cooking on the hot pan after the heat goes off.",
              "symptom": "It's overcooked by the time it reaches the table"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Drop the heat and give it longer. A probe thermometer is the only reliable check for meat.",
              "cause": "Heat too high, browned the outside before the middle warmed through.",
              "symptom": "It's undercooked in the middle"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Reheat covered with a splash of stock or water, on a low heat. Microwave on 60% power if using one, gentler than full blast.",
              "cause": "Reheated uncovered, or no liquid in the pan.",
              "symptom": "The leftovers were dry"
            }
          ],
          "heading": "If something goes wrong"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Variations",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Vegetarian swap: replace meat with mushrooms, lentils, or beans, adjust seasoning to compensate.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Spice version: a pinch of chilli flakes or cracked black pepper at the end shifts the dish without losing its character.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make ahead, freezing, leftovers",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Best fresh. Leftovers keep two days in the fridge; reheat covered with a splash of liquid.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this dish lives",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A British home cook's dish. It sits among the recipes families remember without thinking about, the kind that gets adjusted across generations and never quite the same twice.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
